.TH JOTPAD 1 "2025" "jotpad 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jotpad \- minimal single-note editor with live markdown formatting
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jotpad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Jotpad
is a minimal desktop note editor that manages a single persistent note file.
It auto-saves when typing stops and provides live inline markdown formatting
with clickable hyperlinks.
.PP
On first run, Jotpad prompts for a file location to store the note.
On subsequent runs, it opens the same file automatically.
.SH FEATURES
.IP \(bu 2
Single persistent note file
.IP \(bu 2
Auto-save with 800ms debounce after typing stops
.IP \(bu 2
Live inline markdown formatting (headings, bold, italic, code, links)
.IP \(bu 2
Ctrl+click to open hyperlinks
.IP \(bu 2
Four built-in themes: Dark, Light, Solarized Dark, Solarized Light
.IP \(bu 2
Configurable font family and size
.IP \(bu 2
Markdown formatting can be toggled on/off
.IP \(bu 2
Window size and position remembered across sessions
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/jotpad/config
Configuration file in plain key=value format.
.PP
The configuration file supports the following keys:
.TP
.B theme
One of: dark, light, solarized_dark, solarized_light (default: dark)
.TP
.B font_family
Font family name (default: monospace)
.TP
.B font_size
Font size in pixels (default: 14)
.TP
.B note_path
Absolute path to the note file
.TP
.B markdown_enabled
Enable live markdown formatting: true or false (default: true)
.TP
.B window_width
Window width in pixels
.TP
.B window_height
Window height in pixels
.TP
.B window_x
Window X position
.TP
.B window_y
Window Y position
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
If set, configuration is stored under $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/jotpad/ instead
of ~/.config/jotpad/.
